should make your method and working clear.

(c) what effect will the new tunnel have on the total length of his route? 
 
 
justify your answer.

keith organises two types of children’s activity, ‘sports mad’ and ‘circus fun’.  
 
he needs to determine the number of times each type of activity is to be offered.
 
let x be the number of times he offers the ‘sports mad’ activity. let y be the number of times he 
offers the ‘circus fun’ activity.
 
two constraints are 
 
x - 15
 
 
and 
y > 6
 
these constraints are shown on the graph in figure 6, where the rejected regions are shaded out.
 
(a) explain why y = 6 is shown as a dotted line.
(1)
